WEBVTT

00:01.702 --> 00:02.836
[ Sirens wailing ]

00:02.836 --> 00:04.838
Lucy: 7-Adam-15,
show us on scene

00:04.838 --> 00:06.039
for our hold-up alarm.

00:09.843 --> 00:11.512
Whoa!
Put your hands up!

00:11.512 --> 00:13.080
Nice and slow.
Show us your hands.

00:13.080 --> 00:14.248
Keep your hands up!
Stop right --

00:14.248 --> 00:16.316
You with the bag,
stop where you are

00:16.316 --> 00:18.118
and show us
your hands.

00:18.118 --> 00:19.453
You can see me?

00:19.453 --> 00:21.922
Yes.
Too much of you.

00:21.922 --> 00:24.858
The wizard said this bracelet
would make me invisible.

00:24.858 --> 00:27.094
♪♪

00:27.094 --> 00:28.762
Wait.

00:28.762 --> 00:31.265
You don't see me.

00:31.265 --> 00:32.933
You see the bags.

00:35.669 --> 00:37.070
Oh.
Sir, put your hands up.

00:37.070 --> 00:38.272
No. Wait.

00:38.272 --> 00:40.173
Sir.
It's not -- That --
Keep them up.

00:40.173 --> 00:41.942
Don't even -- Don't --
There it is.

00:41.942 --> 00:43.510
Well, on the bright side,
we can tell

00:43.510 --> 00:45.245
he's not concealing
any weapons.

00:45.245 --> 00:51.084
♪ I'm gonna win for you
like I know you want me to do ♪

00:51.084 --> 00:54.755
♪♪

00:54.755 --> 00:57.157
[ Cellphone chimes, buzzes ]

00:57.157 --> 00:59.993
[ Cellphone chimes, buzzes ]

00:59.993 --> 01:02.129
This is so much harder
than I thought it would be.

01:02.129 --> 01:04.798
If you have an itch, it's okay.
You can scratch it.

01:04.798 --> 01:06.500
No, no, no, no.
[ Cellphone chimes, buzzes ]

01:06.500 --> 01:09.102
This is the longest I've gone
without looking at my phone.

01:09.102 --> 01:10.470
I think
I have a problem.

01:10.470 --> 01:12.205
I wasn't gonna say
anything.

01:12.205 --> 01:13.473
How's it going?

01:13.473 --> 01:15.309
You know, it's going.

01:15.309 --> 01:16.476
Honestly, I don't know.

01:16.476 --> 01:18.712
I-I am not a painter
like you.

01:18.712 --> 01:20.213
Unless you include
painting houses.

01:20.213 --> 01:21.748
Well, I'm not
a painter yet, either.

01:21.748 --> 01:23.383
I've only taken
a few classes.

01:23.383 --> 01:26.153
Believe me --
I am way out of my comfort zone.

01:26.153 --> 01:27.788
Okay, that's what you said
about French cooking.

01:27.788 --> 01:29.957
Then you got that cookbook
and you mastered cassoulet

01:29.957 --> 01:32.259
in three days.
[ Cellphone alarm rings ]

01:32.259 --> 01:34.995
Oh, okay.
Now that one I cannot ignore.

01:34.995 --> 01:36.196
Time for me
to go to work.

01:36.196 --> 01:37.931
Let's see what you got.
No, no, no.

01:37.931 --> 01:40.000
You have to wait
till it's finished.

01:40.000 --> 01:41.802
I'm on tenterhooks.

01:44.304 --> 01:45.739
[ Door opens ]
[ Sighs ]

01:45.739 --> 01:47.240
Hey, you.
Ooh!

01:47.240 --> 01:48.342
Hi. Good morning.

01:48.342 --> 01:51.411
Uh, did you get
my e-mails?
I did.

01:51.411 --> 01:53.280
I haven't had time
to read all the articles

01:53.280 --> 01:56.783
you've sent on coddling felons,
but it's on my to-do list.

01:56.783 --> 01:59.286
Hmm.
Never had a girlfriend
give me homework before.

01:59.286 --> 02:01.788
Well, I give it
because you are as quick

02:01.788 --> 02:04.825
to label people felon as you are
to call me your girlfriend,

02:04.825 --> 02:06.827
when we've only been
on four dates.

02:06.827 --> 02:08.829
Oh, I --
Look, we both know

02:08.829 --> 02:10.397
the prosecutorial system
needs fixing,

02:10.397 --> 02:12.199
and you are in a position
to do that,

02:12.199 --> 02:15.335
which is why I'm...
helping to educate you.

02:15.335 --> 02:16.603
Well, if you feel
this strongly,

02:16.603 --> 02:17.604
why didn't you go
to law school?

02:17.604 --> 02:19.006
My parents wanted me to,

02:19.006 --> 02:20.273
so that was
out of the question.

02:20.273 --> 02:21.174
[ Chuckles ] I'm serious.

02:21.174 --> 02:22.776
I know you love
what you do,

02:22.776 --> 02:24.978
but lots of cops
get tired of the violence

02:24.978 --> 02:26.179
and go to law school.

02:26.179 --> 02:28.815
You could be
part of the solution.

02:28.815 --> 02:30.817
Try not to sound
so condescending.

02:30.817 --> 02:32.653
Yeah, it's hard for me.
Mm-hmm.

02:32.653 --> 02:36.056
I have to get to court.

02:36.056 --> 02:39.493
Did it really bother you
that I said "girlfriend"?

02:39.493 --> 02:42.663
I'm fine with it
as long as you're fine with me

02:42.663 --> 02:45.232
defining you
as my work in progress.

02:45.232 --> 02:46.967
I never know
when you're joking.

02:46.967 --> 02:49.236
Good.
Keeps you on your toes.

02:49.236 --> 02:52.039
♪♪

02:52.039 --> 02:53.240
Oh, hey, Lucy.
Hey.

02:53.240 --> 02:54.641
Hey, uh, did you know
that Bailey

02:54.641 --> 02:56.209
is painting
Nolan's portrait?

02:56.209 --> 02:58.378
Is she?
Gosh, I had no idea.

02:58.378 --> 03:00.647
You only talk about it
all the time.
All the time.

03:00.647 --> 03:02.649
Okay, forgive me for being proud
of my girlfriend.

03:02.649 --> 03:04.351
Look, you got to give me
some lessons.

03:04.351 --> 03:06.520
Like, how are you dating
so far out of your league?

03:06.520 --> 03:08.255
Oh, that --
that's kind of his thing.

03:08.255 --> 03:10.290
Oh. Fair enough.

03:10.290 --> 03:12.459
Seriously, I mean, Bailey --
she's a firefighter,

03:12.459 --> 03:15.429
an army reservist, a capoeira
instructor, and a painter?

03:15.429 --> 03:17.097
You're forgetting
motorcycle racer,

03:17.097 --> 03:19.533
mixologist,
and runner-up for Nobel Prize.

03:19.533 --> 03:21.601
Really?
No. I made the last one up.

03:21.601 --> 03:22.869
But a part of you
believed it.

03:22.869 --> 03:24.404
Yeah.

03:24.404 --> 03:26.006
No uniform today.

03:26.006 --> 03:27.841
What's the occasion?

03:27.841 --> 03:29.509
Oh, you will find out
soon enough.

03:31.912 --> 03:34.881
-Lookin' good, sir.
-Oh! Hey!

03:34.881 --> 03:37.484
Alright, alright.
Settle down.

03:37.484 --> 03:38.652
The suit's for court.

03:38.652 --> 03:40.454
Right now, I want you to focus
on the other person

03:40.454 --> 03:44.491
not in uniform this morning --
Detective Harper.

03:44.491 --> 03:47.294
Anyone want to tell me
why a T. O. would be wearing

03:47.294 --> 03:51.098
her most comfy maternity clothes
out on patrol?

03:51.098 --> 03:53.300
Plain Clothes Day.
Plain Clothes Day.

03:53.300 --> 03:55.368
Okay, what's that?

03:55.368 --> 03:56.269
Today, Detective Harper

03:56.269 --> 03:58.705
will be with you as your shadow,
not your T. O.

03:58.705 --> 04:00.440
Her only job
is to observe.

04:00.440 --> 04:01.942
So act as if
you're on patrol alone

04:01.942 --> 04:04.311
and handle it yourself
accordingly.

04:04.311 --> 04:07.447
Okay. I mean, that actually
sounds kind of awesome.

04:07.447 --> 04:09.316
Oh, by all means,
enjoy it.

04:09.316 --> 04:10.951
And don't let the fact
that it is the day

04:10.951 --> 04:12.986
when the highest percentage
of rookies wash out

04:12.986 --> 04:14.755
bother you at all.

04:14.755 --> 04:17.491
It is?
Sgt. Grey:
Final order of business.

04:17.491 --> 04:20.527
Officer Hong has a dental
emergency this morning.

04:20.527 --> 04:22.529
Nolan, you'll be working
the front desk.

04:22.529 --> 04:24.164
Oh, no problem.
I could use a quiet morning.

04:24.164 --> 04:25.165
With Smitty.

04:25.165 --> 04:29.503
♪♪

04:29.503 --> 04:32.305
I'm sorry, sir.
I can't sign your fix-it ticket

04:32.305 --> 04:34.741
until you actually...
well, fix it.

04:34.741 --> 04:37.978
And when I walked out
of the bank, my bike was gone.

04:37.978 --> 04:39.146
Take it as a sign.

04:39.146 --> 04:40.747
If God wanted us
to ride bikes,

04:40.747 --> 04:42.949
he wouldn't have made
those seats so uncomfortable.

04:42.949 --> 04:45.685
I feel like you're just trying
to avoid writing a report.

04:45.685 --> 04:46.620
I am.

04:46.620 --> 04:48.555
Miss,
if you get in my line,

04:48.555 --> 04:49.556
I can help you
in a minute.

04:49.556 --> 04:51.458
And what can I do
for you today?

04:51.458 --> 04:53.727
My son was mugged for his
skateboard on the way to school.

04:53.727 --> 04:55.362
Oh, I'm sorry
to hear that.

04:55.362 --> 04:58.365
Uh, let's get you
started here.
Thank you.

04:58.365 --> 05:00.233
Hey, hey.
I gotta talk to somebody.

05:00.233 --> 05:02.169
Okay. Well, these people
have been waiting a long time.

05:02.169 --> 05:03.503
If you'll just get
into the line...

05:03.503 --> 05:05.105
[ Slams desk ]
But it's important!

05:05.105 --> 05:06.940
And their case
is important, too.

05:06.940 --> 05:10.310
I-I understand. If you'll
just step into the line, sir.

05:11.511 --> 05:14.214
Thank you.
I apologize for that.

05:14.214 --> 05:17.050
Alright, um, can you tell me
what happened?

05:17.050 --> 05:18.585
Aaron: Seriously, I have
a much greater respect

05:18.585 --> 05:20.153
for what you have
to go through now.

05:20.153 --> 05:22.222
The makeup that I have to wear
for my reality show --

05:22.222 --> 05:23.924
it's killing my skin.

05:26.426 --> 05:28.829
Oh, right.

05:28.829 --> 05:30.230
"You're not here."

05:32.399 --> 05:34.000
Okay,
so this is my shop.

05:35.235 --> 05:36.236
Me.

05:36.236 --> 05:38.405
Alone.

05:38.405 --> 05:40.373
[ Police radio chatter ]

05:40.373 --> 05:43.243
Guess that means I get to choose
what to eat for lunch.

05:44.578 --> 05:45.846
And what to play
on the radio.

05:45.846 --> 05:47.547
[ <i>Bluegrass music plays</i> ]

05:47.547 --> 05:50.383
[ Laughs ]
I'm thinking bluegrass all day.

05:50.383 --> 05:53.086
Then it'll be
your last day.

05:53.086 --> 05:54.421
[ Radio turns off ]

05:54.421 --> 05:56.523
Expired tag.

05:56.523 --> 05:58.625
I'll run the plate.

05:58.625 --> 05:59.626
[ Computer keys clacking ]

05:59.626 --> 06:00.861
[ Beeps ]

06:00.861 --> 06:03.630
It says it belongs
to a Natasha Marsh.

06:03.630 --> 06:05.465
North Hollywood address.

06:05.465 --> 06:06.700
[ Siren chirps ]

06:06.700 --> 06:09.035
Okay.
Let's go say hi.

06:18.445 --> 06:19.779
Morning, ma'am.

06:19.779 --> 06:21.214
Do you know
why I pulled you over?

06:21.214 --> 06:22.415
No, I don't.

06:22.415 --> 06:24.084
Uh,
your tags are expired.

06:24.084 --> 06:26.052
Can you, uh, grab your license
and registration

06:26.052 --> 06:27.654
and step out of the vehicle,
please?

06:27.654 --> 06:29.489
Natasha: I need to get out
of my car for expired tags?

06:29.489 --> 06:30.790
Oh, no, don't worry.
You're not in any trouble.

06:30.790 --> 06:32.492
It's just that there's a lot
of traffic on this street,

06:32.492 --> 06:34.060
and I'm riding solo
today,

06:34.060 --> 06:35.829
so it's not only for my safety,
but for yours, as well.

06:35.829 --> 06:37.464
It will only
take a minute.
Okay.

06:41.268 --> 06:43.470
Here you go.
Right this way.

06:45.472 --> 06:47.274
Alright,
let's see here.

06:47.274 --> 06:48.875
Now, ma'am,
were you aware

06:48.875 --> 06:50.477
that you were driving around
with expired tags?

06:50.477 --> 06:52.479
My husband usually
takes care of that.

06:52.479 --> 06:54.614
Okay, well, look, I'm gonna
give you a warning this time,

06:54.614 --> 06:56.316
but just know,
the next cop that pulls you over

06:56.316 --> 06:58.084
might not be as forgiving,
okay?
[ Engine starts ]

06:58.084 --> 06:59.352
I understand.

06:59.352 --> 07:01.121
Thank you, Officer.
Alright.

07:01.121 --> 07:03.323
Nolan: That was intense.

07:03.323 --> 07:04.524
Would have been
a lot faster

07:04.524 --> 07:05.859
if I hadn't had to help
most of the people.

07:05.859 --> 07:08.695
Well, I'm in the quality,
not quantity business.

07:08.695 --> 07:10.497
Well, you're failing
spectacularly.

07:10.497 --> 07:12.332
Sir, I can help you now.

07:14.901 --> 07:16.670
Sir? Excuse me?

07:18.071 --> 07:20.307
Sir?

07:20.307 --> 07:22.676
Smitty: He okay?

07:22.676 --> 07:24.678
No.

07:24.678 --> 07:25.812
He's dead.

07:25.812 --> 07:28.515
Control, this is Officer Nolan
in the Main Lobby.

07:28.515 --> 07:30.116
We have a person down.

07:30.116 --> 07:31.952
Male in his 40s not conscious,
not breathing,

07:31.952 --> 07:33.353
and cool to the touch.

07:33.353 --> 07:35.956
Repeat -- we have a D. B.
in the Main Lobby.

07:39.960 --> 07:41.728
Tim:
You've been quiet.

07:41.728 --> 07:44.064
What?

07:44.064 --> 07:45.732
Do you think
that I'd be a good lawyer?

07:45.732 --> 07:47.801
[ Chuckles ] No.

07:47.801 --> 07:50.537
And that's a compliment.

07:50.537 --> 07:52.706
Wesley's a lawyer.
We like Wesley.

07:52.706 --> 07:55.542
Eh, we accept Wesley
because we fear Lopez.

07:55.542 --> 07:58.945
[ Scoffs ] It's just...
a progressive D. A.

07:58.945 --> 08:01.548
can change a hell of a lot more
than we can.

08:01.548 --> 08:03.316
We're not here
to change things.

08:03.316 --> 08:04.985
We're here
to catch criminals.

08:04.985 --> 08:07.187
Look, if you want to change
the way society works,

08:07.187 --> 08:08.989
become a billionaire
and eradicate poverty

08:08.989 --> 08:10.156
in Los Angeles.

08:10.156 --> 08:11.391
[ Engine revs, tires squeal ]

08:11.391 --> 08:13.193
What the hell's
that guy doing?

08:13.193 --> 08:15.595
[ Gunshots ]

08:15.595 --> 08:18.765
Shots fired at Spring and First.
We need additional units.

08:18.765 --> 08:20.367
Start RA and airship.

08:20.367 --> 08:22.202
Suspect seen driving
a gray Camaro

08:22.202 --> 08:23.703
last seen going east
on Spring.

08:23.703 --> 08:25.005
[ Tires squeal ]

08:25.005 --> 08:32.345
♪♪

08:32.345 --> 08:35.382
[ Police radio chatter ]

08:37.183 --> 08:38.618
I don't have a pulse.

08:41.454 --> 08:42.622
[ Grunts ]

08:45.592 --> 08:47.193
Put your hands right here
to stop the bleeding.

08:48.728 --> 08:52.198
Pilot: <i>Airship 3 en route.</i>
<i>ETA to scene, 2 minutes.</i>

08:52.198 --> 08:53.733
[ Siren wails ]

08:53.733 --> 08:54.768
There it is.

08:54.768 --> 08:56.569
Control 7-Adam-19,

08:56.569 --> 08:58.338
show me in pursuit
of suspect's vehicle

08:58.338 --> 08:59.572
headed east on Spring.

08:59.572 --> 09:01.541
[ Tires squeal ]

09:01.541 --> 09:04.844
♪♪

09:04.844 --> 09:06.413
Harper: He's going
for the freeway.

09:06.413 --> 09:07.414
Cut him off
before he gets there.

09:07.414 --> 09:08.748
Yeah, I got it.

09:08.748 --> 09:11.217
[ Horn blares ]

09:11.217 --> 09:12.886
Don't lose him.
Yeah, I won't.

09:12.886 --> 09:14.487
[ Tires squeal ]

09:14.487 --> 09:15.722
[ Siren wailing ]

09:15.722 --> 09:22.662
♪♪

09:22.662 --> 09:23.630
[ Horn honks ]

09:23.630 --> 09:25.432
Right. Get to the right.
No, that's the sidewalk.

09:25.432 --> 09:26.232
Harper: So what?!

09:26.232 --> 09:27.300
[ Horn honks ]

09:27.300 --> 09:29.869
[ Tires squealing ]

09:29.869 --> 09:33.740
♪♪

09:33.740 --> 09:36.042
[ Horns honking ]

09:37.210 --> 09:40.246
7-Adam-19, I've lost sight
of the suspect's vehicle.

09:40.246 --> 09:42.248
Last seen headed
to the 110 Freeway.

09:42.248 --> 09:43.783
Do you see him,
Airship 3?

09:43.783 --> 09:45.485
<i>Negative.</i>

09:45.485 --> 09:47.087
♪♪

09:50.690 --> 09:52.826
[ Police radio chatter ]

09:52.826 --> 09:53.793
We got a problem here.

09:55.328 --> 09:57.497
Did I do something wrong
back there?

09:57.497 --> 09:59.833
Harper: I told you to cut right,
and you didn't.

09:59.833 --> 10:01.734
As a civilian,
you are not allowed

10:01.734 --> 10:03.103
to drive
on the sidewalk.

10:03.103 --> 10:06.439
As a cop, you do it
to catch a killer.

10:06.439 --> 10:09.642
Benches and -- and parking
meters are replaceable.

10:09.642 --> 10:11.911
Right. Sorry.

10:11.911 --> 10:13.279
Anything come back
on the shooter's plates?

10:13.279 --> 10:14.781
Yeah,
stolen this morning.

10:14.781 --> 10:17.650
And I'm sure we'll find the car
dumped within the hour.

10:17.650 --> 10:19.953
What have we got?
Drive-by.

10:19.953 --> 10:22.288
The victim passed away
before the paramedics came.

10:22.288 --> 10:24.324
Did you get a look
at the shooter?

10:24.324 --> 10:25.892
Not a good one.

10:25.892 --> 10:26.826
[ Police radio chatter ]

10:26.826 --> 10:28.728
Then we start with her.

10:28.728 --> 10:32.065
Was this just road rage, or did
someone target her for a reason?

10:32.065 --> 10:34.868
Nolan: So, the guy in the hoodie
sits next to our victim,

10:34.868 --> 10:36.469
injects him
with something,

10:36.469 --> 10:37.837
and then walks away.

10:37.837 --> 10:39.305
M.E.
is rushing toxicology,

10:39.305 --> 10:40.940
but given how fast
the victim reacted,

10:40.940 --> 10:42.809
it's got to be
a poison of some kind.

10:42.809 --> 10:44.544
A killer willing
to commit murder

10:44.544 --> 10:46.112
right in front
of our eyes

10:46.112 --> 10:47.814
is either really brave
or really desperate.

10:47.814 --> 10:50.517
And neither of them
is good.
No.

10:50.517 --> 10:53.720
Hey. Sorry I'm late. Had to get
TID squared away on that 187.

10:53.720 --> 10:55.755
Just heard they were
delayed because they had
to come here first?

10:55.755 --> 10:57.857
People are committing murder
right under our noses now.

10:57.857 --> 10:59.492
Under <i>my</i> nose.

10:59.492 --> 11:00.927
I'm sorry your first stint
as Watch Commander

11:00.927 --> 11:02.395
is under
these circumstances.

11:02.395 --> 11:03.696
No worries.
I'll hold down the fort

11:03.696 --> 11:05.765
until you're back.
Alright.

11:05.765 --> 11:07.734
Officer Hong is managing
the front desk now.

11:07.734 --> 11:08.735
What do you want me
to do?

11:08.735 --> 11:10.136
Stay on
the poisoning victim,

11:10.136 --> 11:11.171
coordinate
with the detectives.

11:11.171 --> 11:12.305
Yes, sir.
Yeah.

11:13.907 --> 11:15.875
Look, I've learned
my lesson, okay?

11:15.875 --> 11:19.245
Trash cans, benches,
bus kiosks -- it's all property.

11:19.245 --> 11:20.980
I'm not gonna hesitate
next time.

11:20.980 --> 11:23.349
Not bus kiosks.
Those things are shop killers.

11:23.349 --> 11:25.185
Alright, so, the guy
that had the camera --

11:25.185 --> 11:29.389
his S. U. V. was registered
to a business, Mad Profitz, Inc.

11:29.389 --> 11:31.891
Are you sure
he was filming us?

11:31.891 --> 11:34.594
I mean, this is L. A.,
the Land of Paparazzi.

11:34.594 --> 11:36.896
Maybe Doja Cat was getting
a boba tea or something.

11:36.896 --> 11:39.599
No, I know for a fact
that he was there for us.

11:39.599 --> 11:43.169
How?
'Cause he's tailing us
right now -- him and a driver.

11:43.169 --> 11:44.871
What?

11:44.871 --> 11:46.206
Oh, well, let me flip around.
I'll pull their ass over.

11:46.206 --> 11:48.775
No, no.
Don't let on that you know.

11:48.775 --> 11:51.277
I got a better way
of flushing them out.

11:51.277 --> 11:53.580
Speed up here
and make a right on the corner.

11:53.580 --> 11:56.416
♪♪

11:56.416 --> 11:57.884
[ Tires squeal ]

11:57.884 --> 12:04.791
♪♪

12:04.791 --> 12:11.965
♪♪

12:11.965 --> 12:18.805
♪♪

12:18.805 --> 12:21.107
Hey. LAPD.
What are you doing?

12:21.107 --> 12:24.777
Detective Harper.
It is so good to see you again.

12:24.777 --> 12:28.114
Wait. You're --
You're that TV producer.

12:28.114 --> 12:29.048
Aaron: Morris.

12:29.048 --> 12:30.917
Hey, man.
You look good.

12:30.917 --> 12:32.652
D-Did you know
about this?

12:32.652 --> 12:35.021
No. So, what's up, man?
Y'all been filming us?

12:35.021 --> 12:36.589
Morris: Well, look, I mean,
you wouldn't give us access

12:36.589 --> 12:37.824
to the station,
and we needed B-roll,

12:37.824 --> 12:39.025
so your mom said,
"Get it done."

12:39.025 --> 12:41.494
Unh-unh. No, no.
This ends now.

12:41.494 --> 12:43.029
W-What you all
are doing is --

12:43.029 --> 12:45.465
It's perfectly legal,
and you know it.

12:45.465 --> 12:47.033
Look, as a producer
on the show,

12:47.033 --> 12:48.234
you should
really appreciate

12:48.234 --> 12:50.436
the production value
this gives us.

12:50.436 --> 12:51.838
I mean,
quick question.

12:51.838 --> 12:53.006
Is it at all possible
we could reshoot

12:53.006 --> 12:54.574
this whole
car-chase thing?

12:54.574 --> 12:55.842
I'd really love to get
a few more angles.

12:55.842 --> 12:58.478
♪♪

12:58.478 --> 12:59.946
Let's go, Boot.
Yeah.

13:00.947 --> 13:03.249
Hey, man,
thanks for jammin' me up.

13:03.249 --> 13:05.485
You might be filming my last day
on the job.

13:05.485 --> 13:06.819
So good for you.

13:06.819 --> 13:10.223
♪♪

13:10.223 --> 13:12.325
There was a murder
at the front desk?

13:12.325 --> 13:15.028
Not just a murder.
A poisoning.

13:15.028 --> 13:16.963
In a police station?
Who does that?

13:16.963 --> 13:18.865
Uh, the villain
in a Bond movie?

13:18.865 --> 13:21.267
Any motive yet?
According to the family,

13:21.267 --> 13:23.469
the victim was paranoid
someone was following him

13:23.469 --> 13:26.005
because he was about to testify
before a grand jury.

13:26.005 --> 13:28.474
In what case?
I'm trying
to find that out.

13:28.474 --> 13:29.876
I heard
you caught a homicide.

13:29.876 --> 13:31.511
Yeah.
It's been a busy morning.

13:31.511 --> 13:33.880
Hey, guys. I ordered
way too many egg rolls,

13:33.880 --> 13:36.282
so help yourself.

13:36.282 --> 13:37.717
Okay, thanks.

13:38.518 --> 13:40.320
Lucy, your drive-by
wasn't road rage.

13:40.320 --> 13:41.654
It was a hit.

13:41.654 --> 13:42.989
The victim was on her way
to testify

13:42.989 --> 13:44.991
before Matteo Rubio's
grand jury.

13:46.859 --> 13:48.027
Lopez:
We've got a problem.

13:48.027 --> 13:50.330
Your drive-by shooting
and my front-desk poisoning

13:50.330 --> 13:52.732
were both scheduled to testify
before the grand jury today.

13:52.732 --> 13:55.301
In what case?
The RICO case
against Matteo Rubio.

13:55.301 --> 13:57.904
Grey's a witness in that case.
He's on his way to testify now.

13:57.904 --> 14:00.073
♪♪

14:00.073 --> 14:01.307
Straight to voicemail.

14:04.043 --> 14:05.211
[ Engine shuts off ]

14:10.149 --> 14:11.584
[ Alarm chirps ]

14:18.758 --> 14:20.259
[ Car door closes ]

14:27.367 --> 14:29.268
Forget my head
if it wasn't attached.

14:29.268 --> 14:31.337
That's what my dad
used to always say.

14:31.337 --> 14:32.872
Now you're making me
feel old.
Oh, boy.

14:32.872 --> 14:33.906
I'm a police officer.

14:33.906 --> 14:35.908
You're carrying a concealed
weapon into a courthouse.

14:35.908 --> 14:37.944
You're right.
I was.

14:37.944 --> 14:40.513
But now I don't have to,
'cause you're right here.

14:40.513 --> 14:42.749
[ Groans ]

14:42.749 --> 14:44.684
[ Gunshots ]

14:44.684 --> 14:51.824
♪♪

14:51.824 --> 14:58.998
♪♪

14:58.998 --> 15:05.938
♪♪

15:05.938 --> 15:08.941
[ Gasping ]

15:08.941 --> 15:11.277
[ Panting ]

15:11.277 --> 15:12.779
[ Groans ]

15:12.779 --> 15:14.580
♪♪

15:14.580 --> 15:16.115
[ Groans ]

15:16.115 --> 15:19.018
♪♪

15:19.018 --> 15:20.987
Come on. Come on.

15:26.092 --> 15:30.430
[ Monitor alarm ]

15:30.430 --> 15:32.999
[ Paddles whir, thud ]

15:32.999 --> 15:34.967
Dr. Jones: Stand clear.

15:34.967 --> 15:35.968
Clear.

15:35.968 --> 15:38.638
[ Flatline ]

15:38.638 --> 15:41.073
[ Monitor beeping ]

15:41.073 --> 15:43.075
Nurse Lisa: I need you
to focus on me, Sergeant.

15:43.075 --> 15:44.410
Can you do that?

15:46.179 --> 15:47.980
What? Yes. Yes.
Clear.

15:47.980 --> 15:50.016
Are you having
any trouble breathing?

15:50.016 --> 15:52.885
No.

15:52.885 --> 15:55.688
Pupils fixed and dilated.
I'm calling it.

15:55.688 --> 15:58.057
Time of death -- 16:42.

15:58.057 --> 15:59.959
Did you hit your head
at any point?

16:01.661 --> 16:03.996
What?
Did you hit your head?

16:03.996 --> 16:05.465
No. No.

16:05.465 --> 16:08.367
Um, I-I-I don't think so.

16:08.367 --> 16:11.204
What do we got?
Knife wound to the face --
gonna need stitches.

16:11.204 --> 16:12.872
GSW to
the left shoulder --

16:12.872 --> 16:14.640
looks like a
through-and-through.

16:14.640 --> 16:17.043
Vitals are good.
Alright. Alright,
let's get him up to the O. R.

16:17.043 --> 16:18.478
Surgeon needs
to get in there,

16:18.478 --> 16:20.046
make sure
there's no internal damage,

16:20.046 --> 16:21.380
clean everything up,
okay?

16:21.380 --> 16:23.015
Okay.

16:24.016 --> 16:27.520
Hey, Doc, how is he?

16:27.520 --> 16:29.055
He's lucky.

16:34.227 --> 16:36.262
Hey.

16:36.262 --> 16:38.264
They're gonna
fix you up, okay?

16:39.665 --> 16:42.869
Yeah, yeah.
Um...

16:42.869 --> 16:44.370
Um...you --

16:44.370 --> 16:48.508
you need to alert
Captain Maddux.

16:48.508 --> 16:50.843
Yeah, already did.
Everything's squared away.

16:50.843 --> 16:53.479
You just focus
on getting better, alright?

16:54.714 --> 16:57.316
Tim?
Yeah?

16:57.316 --> 17:00.052
Who was she?

17:00.052 --> 17:03.055
A hitter
for Matteo Rubio.

17:03.055 --> 17:05.725
And we think she's the shooter
from our drive-by.

17:11.964 --> 17:14.066
She was so fast.

17:23.209 --> 17:26.045
Nolan: Here he is.
How is he?

17:26.045 --> 17:29.048
They just took him into surgery.
Uh, he's in shock.

17:29.048 --> 17:30.216
Wound seems superficial,
but they won't know for sure

17:30.216 --> 17:31.684
until they open him up.

17:31.684 --> 17:33.286
And the shooter?
She didn't make it.

17:33.286 --> 17:34.654
Okay,
so, is the threat over?

17:34.654 --> 17:36.155
I don't think so.

17:36.155 --> 17:38.291
The killer at the front desk
was definitely a man.

17:38.291 --> 17:40.259
I don't understand.
Grand juries are secret.

17:40.259 --> 17:42.461
How did Rubio get his hands
on a witness list?

17:42.461 --> 17:44.297
I'm gonna circle back
to A. D. A. Del Monte.

17:44.297 --> 17:47.333
We need to find out who else was
set to testify against Rubio.

17:47.333 --> 17:48.868
Okay, good.
Take Lucy with you.

17:48.868 --> 17:50.236
Hey, I'll stay here, text you
when he's out of surgery.

17:50.236 --> 17:51.771
Thanks.

17:51.771 --> 17:53.773
Alright, listen up.
Everybody, listen up.

17:53.773 --> 17:55.274
I want 'round-the-clock
security.

17:55.274 --> 17:57.276
These people were bold enough
to go after a cop.

17:57.276 --> 17:58.911
They're not just gonna
stand down now.

17:58.911 --> 18:00.713
Got it?
-Okay, copy.

18:00.713 --> 18:02.548
Because this is
an officer-involved shooting,

18:02.548 --> 18:04.750
I'm gonna need to stay here
as Grey's union delegate.

18:04.750 --> 18:06.319
Okay. Do you know
what you have to do?
Yes, sir.

18:06.319 --> 18:08.521
Uh,
procedurally at least.

18:08.521 --> 18:10.523
I-I don't know
what I'm gonna say to him.

18:10.523 --> 18:12.525
He was with you
after your shooting.

18:12.525 --> 18:14.293
Yeah. He's the reason
I made it through.

18:14.293 --> 18:15.828
Yeah.
So do what he did.

18:15.828 --> 18:17.296
He's always been there
for us.

18:17.296 --> 18:18.965
Now it's time
to return the favor.

18:18.965 --> 18:20.600
And update me the moment
he gets out of surgery.

18:20.600 --> 18:22.335
Yes, sir.
What are you gonna do?

18:22.335 --> 18:23.970
I'm gonna try and I. D.
our deceased shooter,

18:23.970 --> 18:25.972
see if I can find out
who she was partnered with.

18:27.473 --> 18:29.809
What Tim said --

18:29.809 --> 18:32.778
You've killed someone
in the line of duty?

18:32.778 --> 18:35.581
Yeah.
A month into my rookie year.

18:35.581 --> 18:37.583
I didn't know that.

18:37.583 --> 18:39.652
I don't talk about it
much.

18:39.652 --> 18:41.053
I get it.

18:41.053 --> 18:43.456
Um, we work jobs
that bring us face-to-face

18:43.456 --> 18:45.057
with death every day.

18:45.057 --> 18:48.661
But it's different
when it's because of you.

18:48.661 --> 18:50.196
Army Reserve.

18:50.196 --> 18:53.366
I did a tour
right when I signed up.

18:53.366 --> 18:56.102
Every time I think
I got a handle on you...

18:57.336 --> 18:59.171
Listen, do you want me
to stay with you?

18:59.171 --> 19:00.439
I can call in a sub.

19:00.439 --> 19:01.641
No.
You go back to work.

19:01.641 --> 19:03.009
I got Wesley
to keep me company.

19:03.009 --> 19:04.210
Okay.

19:04.210 --> 19:05.611
Love you.
Alright. Love you.

19:09.615 --> 19:12.218
Okay.
Yeah, thanks.

19:12.218 --> 19:13.686
That was Tim.

19:13.686 --> 19:17.223
Grey's in surgery, but the wound
is not life-threatening.

19:17.223 --> 19:18.858
Thank God.

19:18.858 --> 19:22.228
[ Police radio chatter ]

19:22.228 --> 19:24.096
This feels petty to ask,

19:24.096 --> 19:26.232
but I'm not passing
Plain Clothes Day, am I?

19:26.232 --> 19:28.567
It hasn't been
a good start.

19:28.567 --> 19:31.070
But I could still
finish strong, right?

19:31.070 --> 19:34.173
I'd focus on getting to the end
of shift with no more drama.

19:36.308 --> 19:37.543
Uh-oh.

19:37.543 --> 19:39.011
Rolled right through
a stop sign.

19:39.011 --> 19:40.546
[ Siren chirps ]

19:53.426 --> 19:55.928
Afternoon, sir.
You know why I pulled you over?

19:57.463 --> 19:59.265
Mr. Hayes.
I heard you were a cop.

19:59.265 --> 20:00.533
I thought it was a joke.

20:00.533 --> 20:02.034
No, um...

20:02.034 --> 20:04.103
I think about you
every day,

20:04.103 --> 20:06.272
what I'd say to you,
what I'd...do to you.

20:06.272 --> 20:07.339
Okay, sir, stop.

20:07.339 --> 20:08.607
What?
You'll arrest me?

20:08.607 --> 20:10.109
Go. Get -- Get closer,
get closer.

20:10.109 --> 20:11.711
-Sir, stop.
-I can say whatever I want.

20:11.711 --> 20:13.245
Hey, hey, what are you doing?
What are you doing?

20:13.245 --> 20:14.413
Dexter: Look at you.
You're -- You're a disgrace.

20:14.413 --> 20:17.116
That's Patrick Hayes' dad.

20:17.116 --> 20:19.318
The kid Aaron was accused
of killing?

20:19.318 --> 20:20.653
Alright, stay back.

20:20.653 --> 20:21.954
Are you kidding?
This is gold.

20:21.954 --> 20:23.489
I would never hurt Patrick,
okay?

20:23.489 --> 20:24.724
He was my best friend.

20:24.724 --> 20:27.126
Excuse me, sir.
I am Detective Harper.

20:27.126 --> 20:28.661
This is Aaron.
He is my trainee.

20:28.661 --> 20:30.296
Do you know who he is?
He murdered my son.

20:30.296 --> 20:31.731
I know
about the allegations.

20:31.731 --> 20:33.733
Allegations?! Yeah, you might
have fooled the police,

20:33.733 --> 20:35.468
but I know what you are.

20:35.468 --> 20:36.469
I see through you.

20:38.437 --> 20:40.539
Who are you with? TMZ?

20:40.539 --> 20:43.476
Yeah, you never get tired
of feeding on my grief,
do you, you vultures?!

20:43.476 --> 20:45.277
Morris, what are you doing, man?
Get him out of here.
Alright.

20:45.277 --> 20:47.279
Out of here now.
You know them?

20:47.279 --> 20:48.414
You set this up!

20:48.414 --> 20:50.282
No. Mr. Hayes, listen.
I-I swear, okay?

20:50.282 --> 20:51.617
My mom's doing a show,

20:51.617 --> 20:52.918
but I don't have anything to do
with this, okay?

20:52.918 --> 20:54.520
Y-You're making money
off of this?!

20:54.520 --> 20:56.422
Conversation.
You're making a show?!

20:56.422 --> 20:58.958
♪♪

20:58.958 --> 21:01.160
Morris:
This is a live arrest.

21:01.160 --> 21:02.962
Mr. Hayes,
I'm sorry, okay?

21:02.962 --> 21:04.163
I didn't mean
for any of this to happen.

21:04.163 --> 21:05.598
I'm sorry.

21:05.598 --> 21:07.166
[ Handcuffs click ]

21:10.603 --> 21:13.339
All the other witnesses
have been taken into
protective custody.

21:13.339 --> 21:15.274
We need to put
undercover officers on
their home addresses.

21:15.274 --> 21:17.143
Odds are good the assassin
will target another witness,

21:17.143 --> 21:19.178
and we need to be set up
to catch them.

21:19.178 --> 21:20.646
I can't do that.
You know that.

21:20.646 --> 21:22.348
You know the grand juries
are secret.

21:22.348 --> 21:24.517
That's why the D. A.'s office
handles all witness security.

21:24.517 --> 21:27.186
You're doing
a bang-up job so far.

21:27.186 --> 21:29.188
Look, I'm gonna chalk
that one up

21:29.188 --> 21:31.557
to misplaced anger
over what happened to Wade.

21:31.557 --> 21:33.459
The best way to keep
our witnesses safe

21:33.459 --> 21:35.528
is for them
to catch Rubio's hit men.

21:35.528 --> 21:37.396
If the list helps them do that,
why not share it?

21:37.396 --> 21:39.532
Because it doesn't work
that way.

21:39.532 --> 21:41.000
Look, I'm sorry.
I am, okay?

21:41.000 --> 21:43.369
But the case against Rubio
is far from guaranteed.

21:43.369 --> 21:44.870
I have to protect it.

21:44.870 --> 21:46.672
Now, if you can bring me
some sort of definitive proof

21:46.672 --> 21:48.307
that he's behind
these attacks,

21:48.307 --> 21:50.609
well, that's
a different story.

21:50.609 --> 21:51.777
Then that's
what I'll do.

21:51.777 --> 21:53.112
Fine.

22:00.820 --> 22:02.388
It's not right.

22:04.590 --> 22:06.392
He's not dangerous.

22:08.394 --> 22:11.063
If it was any other cop, he
would have never thrown a punch.

22:14.033 --> 22:15.901
I created that situation.

22:19.338 --> 22:21.006
We should let him go.

22:21.006 --> 22:22.908
It's your arrest,
your call.

22:25.411 --> 22:27.012
[ Exhales deeply ]

22:27.012 --> 22:28.848
Can you get me
Dexter Hayes' belongings?

22:33.052 --> 22:34.420
What are you doing?

22:34.420 --> 22:37.189
I'll handle it from here.
It's Plain Clothes Day.

22:37.189 --> 22:38.891
I mean, you're not supposed
to help me.

22:38.891 --> 22:42.194
Plain Clothes Day
is over.

22:42.194 --> 22:43.896
Look, nothing good
will come from you

22:43.896 --> 22:46.198
talking
to Patrick's dad again.

22:47.566 --> 22:48.868
Okay.

22:48.868 --> 22:50.569
Go do your paperwork
somewhere else.

22:50.569 --> 22:51.937
I'll find you after.

23:00.446 --> 23:01.947
[ Door buzzes ]

23:02.882 --> 23:04.350
What's going on?

23:06.452 --> 23:09.588
The murderer couldn't
bother to stick around
to see me go to jail?

23:09.588 --> 23:11.891
Uh, no, he actually asked
that I release you.

23:11.891 --> 23:15.294
And I will recommend
that the D. A. not charge.

23:15.294 --> 23:17.563
It's the best we can do.

23:17.563 --> 23:19.565
He shouldn't even
be a cop.

23:19.565 --> 23:23.402
Aaron's a liar,
a sick human being.

23:23.402 --> 23:25.204
I took him into my home.

23:27.106 --> 23:30.276
Every time his parents went
on some month-long vacation,

23:30.276 --> 23:32.478
where -- where do you think
he lived?

23:32.478 --> 23:34.313
[ Sighs ]

23:34.313 --> 23:35.915
He was like
another son to me.

23:35.915 --> 23:36.982
He...

23:39.952 --> 23:41.487
That was all a lie.

23:43.522 --> 23:45.291
And he killed my boy.

23:48.027 --> 23:51.931
Look, uh, there is nothing
that I can say

23:51.931 --> 23:54.333
that is gonna make you
change your mind.

23:55.901 --> 24:01.507
Best thing I can do is
to offer my sincere condolences.

24:08.847 --> 24:11.350
Lucy.
Can I grab you for a second?

24:11.350 --> 24:13.152
Uh...
Make it quick.

24:17.356 --> 24:18.657
Right here.

24:23.195 --> 24:24.730
What's going on?

24:29.268 --> 24:31.136
What is this?

24:31.136 --> 24:33.539
The list of witnesses
in the Rubio grand jury.

24:33.539 --> 24:35.174
Wow. I-I --

24:35.174 --> 24:37.609
But you can't tell anyone
you got it from me.

24:37.609 --> 24:38.944
I'm serious.

24:38.944 --> 24:40.713
Del Monte would fire me
on the spot.

24:40.713 --> 24:42.181
Maybe even prosecute me

24:42.181 --> 24:43.515
for leaking
confidential information.

24:43.515 --> 24:45.584
Stop. You can't do this.
I won't let you.

24:45.584 --> 24:47.753
But you need this
to catch the guy.

24:47.753 --> 24:49.388
People are dead.
And if this --

24:49.388 --> 24:51.557
We can't catch a criminal
by becoming criminals.

24:51.557 --> 24:52.891
I...

24:56.228 --> 24:57.830
We'll find another way.

24:59.732 --> 25:01.200
Okay.

25:04.003 --> 25:05.704
They just I. D.'d
Grey's shooter.

25:07.506 --> 25:08.807
[ Monitor beeping ]

25:08.807 --> 25:11.643
[ Knock on door ]
Sir.

25:11.643 --> 25:13.679
Hey. Hey.
Come in.

25:13.679 --> 25:16.348
[ Clears throat ]
How you feeling?

25:16.348 --> 25:18.384
Like I got shot.

25:20.185 --> 25:21.587
Talk to Luna yet?

25:21.587 --> 25:23.622
She's in Montreal.

25:23.622 --> 25:25.624
And I figured this is a
conversation you want to have

25:25.624 --> 25:28.027
in person
when she gets back.

25:28.027 --> 25:31.230
You know, uh,
a wise man once told me,

25:31.230 --> 25:33.799
"This is not something
you want your family

25:33.799 --> 25:36.335
to hear on the news."

25:36.335 --> 25:38.771
You're right.
I'll call her.

25:38.771 --> 25:40.439
[ Sighs ]

25:40.439 --> 25:43.242
And she will tear my head off
once she knows I'm okay.

25:43.242 --> 25:45.044
When I became
Watch Commander,

25:45.044 --> 25:46.578
I promised
she and Dominique

25:46.578 --> 25:49.048
wouldn't have to worry
about me anymore.

25:49.048 --> 25:52.151
It was out of your control.
She'll understand.

25:52.151 --> 25:54.787
She'll want to install cameras
in your office

25:54.787 --> 25:57.256
to keep an eye on you,
but she'll understand.

25:57.256 --> 25:58.791
Yeah.

25:58.791 --> 26:00.259
Hey, let me take care
of that.

26:02.895 --> 26:07.399
Um, yeah, it's official --
everything hurts.

26:07.399 --> 26:09.034
Do --
Do you need anything?

26:09.034 --> 26:10.402
No, no, no.

26:10.402 --> 26:11.804
I don't --

26:14.706 --> 26:16.375
How do you do it?

26:16.375 --> 26:18.077
I mean,
we're the same age.

26:18.077 --> 26:20.446
Ish.

26:20.446 --> 26:23.148
So how do you go out patrolling
the streets

26:23.148 --> 26:26.485
and chasing suspects,

26:26.485 --> 26:29.321
getting into shootouts
day in, day out?

26:29.321 --> 26:30.689
Tylenol and Icy Hot.

26:31.924 --> 26:34.326
Huh.

26:34.326 --> 26:37.196
It wasn't
like this before.

26:37.196 --> 26:38.764
The last time I got shot,

26:38.764 --> 26:41.333
I pulled out my own I. V. s

26:41.333 --> 26:43.435
and checked myself out.

26:43.435 --> 26:44.837
[ Chuckles ]

26:47.306 --> 26:49.975
Now I-I can't even
imagine it.

26:51.410 --> 26:53.679
Maybe that's the --

26:53.679 --> 26:55.114
Maybe that's
the difference.

26:55.114 --> 26:56.648
I was never that guy.

26:56.648 --> 26:58.117
I don't know what it's like
to be a cop

26:58.117 --> 27:01.353
and not go home aching
at the end of every shift.

27:01.353 --> 27:03.155
So what you're saying is,

27:03.155 --> 27:05.824
I need to accept the fact
that I'm old.

27:05.824 --> 27:08.327
Mm.

27:08.327 --> 27:11.697
I used to think about it
all the time coming up...

27:14.366 --> 27:18.103
...how I'd react
to taking a life.

27:18.103 --> 27:23.675
♪♪

27:23.675 --> 27:27.279
Then year by year
went by,

27:27.279 --> 27:28.447
and, uh...

27:31.783 --> 27:33.352
...I guess I thought...

27:35.154 --> 27:36.688
...I made it.

27:38.357 --> 27:40.359
I'd never have
to go through this.

27:40.359 --> 27:43.929
You didn't have
a choice.

27:43.929 --> 27:45.931
She was going
to kill you.

27:45.931 --> 27:49.535
And any of us
would have done the same.

27:51.904 --> 27:53.739
Right.

27:53.739 --> 27:58.343
That doesn't help now,
but it -- it will later.

27:59.811 --> 28:01.914
What will help now?

28:03.348 --> 28:04.750
Nothing.

28:06.885 --> 28:08.554
This part's just hard.

28:08.554 --> 28:16.395
♪♪

28:19.798 --> 28:21.200
Any movement?

28:21.200 --> 28:22.734
Lucy: No.

28:22.734 --> 28:23.869
[ Dog barking in distance ]

28:28.740 --> 28:31.176
[ Car doors closing ]

28:31.176 --> 28:33.178
Alright,
thanks for coming out.

28:33.178 --> 28:35.013
Our target is six houses up
on the right --

28:35.013 --> 28:36.582
851 West Waverley.

28:36.582 --> 28:39.418
It's a ShareBNB rented by our
deceased suspect, Jane Becker.

28:39.418 --> 28:41.053
Now, Becker had a partner --
unknown male.

28:41.053 --> 28:42.788
It's possible he's in the house
we're hitting.

28:42.788 --> 28:43.755
Lucy: Cut the power.

28:43.755 --> 28:45.757
LAPD!
We have a search warrant!

28:45.757 --> 28:47.125
Open the door now!

28:47.125 --> 28:55.767
♪♪

28:55.767 --> 29:04.042
♪♪

29:04.042 --> 29:12.684
♪♪

29:12.684 --> 29:14.253
Tim:
Alright, house is clear.

29:14.253 --> 29:16.455
Advise DWP
to restore the power.

29:16.455 --> 29:18.657
Do you smell smoke?

29:18.657 --> 29:20.025
Yeah.

29:20.025 --> 29:22.761
It's a little hot outside
to be having a fire.

29:24.663 --> 29:26.098
Tim: Looks like
we just missed him.

29:28.300 --> 29:31.436
And he burned up some evidence
before he left.

29:31.436 --> 29:33.272
Yeah.

29:33.272 --> 29:34.906
Not much to work with.

29:36.842 --> 29:38.010
Mm.

29:43.682 --> 29:45.250
Kellen Myers.

29:46.852 --> 29:49.221
[ Police radio chatter ]

29:51.523 --> 29:54.226
What's going on here?
It's -- It's almost midnight.

29:54.226 --> 29:56.295
Y-You know I'm an officer
of the court, right?

29:56.295 --> 29:58.730
You're a paralegal,
and you're in serious trouble.

29:58.730 --> 30:00.032
I'm calling a lawyer.

30:00.032 --> 30:01.867
Great.
You can show her these.

30:01.867 --> 30:04.870
Your bank statements
for the last six months.

30:04.870 --> 30:07.939
You received four payments
of $2,500 each

30:07.939 --> 30:10.008
from Cayman Cities
Holding Corporation.

30:10.008 --> 30:12.311
That's Matteo Rubio's
dummy corporation.

30:12.311 --> 30:15.947
You sold him the list
of the grand jury's witnesses.

30:15.947 --> 30:17.883
Rubio? I-I don't even know
who that is.

30:17.883 --> 30:20.485
I don't have time
to play games!

30:20.485 --> 30:23.088
Two people are dead,
a cop's in the hospital,

30:23.088 --> 30:26.325
and you're an accessory
to all of it!

30:28.226 --> 30:30.162
I didn't know.

30:30.162 --> 30:32.097
I-I thought they were just
gonna scare people.

30:32.097 --> 30:35.067
I-I-I had no idea
anyone was gonna get killed.

30:36.468 --> 30:38.403
Listen to me.

30:38.403 --> 30:41.340
You have one chance
to make this right.

30:41.340 --> 30:43.875
I need you to tell me
who they are,

30:43.875 --> 30:47.346
where they are, and what exactly
did you tell them.

30:47.346 --> 30:51.049
♪♪

30:51.049 --> 30:53.952
They wanted a list of the names
of the witnesses.

30:56.121 --> 30:57.556
And the prosecutor.

30:59.124 --> 31:01.126
Any luck getting through
to the D. A.'s office?

31:01.126 --> 31:03.128
Dispatcher: <i>No.</i>
<i>Phone lines appear to be down.</i>

31:03.128 --> 31:05.764
That can't be a coincidence.
I'm calling Chris.

31:05.764 --> 31:06.965
[ Engine starts ]

31:06.965 --> 31:08.967
[ <i>Ringing</i> ]

31:08.967 --> 31:11.169
♪♪

31:11.169 --> 31:13.905
[ Sirens wailing ]

31:13.905 --> 31:16.441
♪♪

31:16.441 --> 31:17.743
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

31:17.743 --> 31:19.344
Chris: The D. A.
hasn't even considered

31:19.344 --> 31:20.946
postponing
tomorrow's testimony?

31:20.946 --> 31:22.748
Two people are dead,

31:22.748 --> 31:24.349
and one of the killers
is still out there.

31:24.349 --> 31:27.052
Yeah, all the more reason
to keep the grand jury convened.

31:27.052 --> 31:29.087
Get Rubio behind bars
as soon as possible.

31:29.087 --> 31:31.490
You think the case still has
legs with two dead witnesses?

31:31.490 --> 31:34.960
[ Sighs ] Well, it's a setback,
but we did our homework.

31:34.960 --> 31:36.628
You know,
we have our evidence.

31:36.628 --> 31:38.997
Most importantly,
the rest of the witnesses

31:38.997 --> 31:40.332
are in protective custody,
so...

31:40.332 --> 31:42.467
[ Vibrating continues ]

31:42.467 --> 31:43.602
[ <i>Ringing</i> ]

31:43.602 --> 31:45.537
He's not answering.
Try again.

31:45.537 --> 31:47.773
[ Siren wailing ]

31:47.773 --> 31:49.141
[ <i>Ringing</i> ]

31:49.141 --> 31:51.143
[ Tires squeal ]

31:51.143 --> 31:53.779
♪♪

31:53.779 --> 31:55.981
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

31:55.981 --> 31:57.783
Hey, it bothers you
that I didn't share intel

31:57.783 --> 32:00.419
with the LAPD,
doesn't it?

32:00.419 --> 32:02.954
No.

32:02.954 --> 32:04.823
I mean, yeah.

32:04.823 --> 32:07.159
We're on the same side,
right?

32:07.159 --> 32:08.427
Mostly.

32:08.427 --> 32:10.262
But LAPD leaks like
a sieve,

32:10.262 --> 32:12.464
so we gotta play everything
close to the vest.

32:12.464 --> 32:14.132
[ Vibrating continues ]
That's my phone.

32:17.135 --> 32:18.236
Lucy.

32:18.236 --> 32:20.806
Chris, um,
where are you?

32:20.806 --> 32:22.307
At the office.
Why?

32:22.307 --> 32:24.176
Is Del Monte with you?
Yeah.

32:24.176 --> 32:27.012
Okay, listen.
Someone is coming to kill him.

32:27.012 --> 32:28.613
What?

32:28.613 --> 32:30.649
<i>You have to get him</i>
<i>out of there.</i>

32:30.649 --> 32:31.817
<i>Chris?</i>

32:34.052 --> 32:35.854
The lights
just went out.

32:35.854 --> 32:37.355
They just cut the power.
How far away are we?

32:37.355 --> 32:38.657
Three minutes.

32:38.657 --> 32:40.559
Chris, you need to hide.

32:40.559 --> 32:42.461
I got to warn Del Monte.

32:42.461 --> 32:43.795
No, Chris.

32:43.795 --> 32:47.065
♪♪

32:50.635 --> 33:00.479
♪♪

33:00.479 --> 33:10.322
♪♪

33:10.322 --> 33:20.198
♪♪

33:20.198 --> 33:30.208
♪♪

33:30.208 --> 33:40.085
♪♪

33:40.085 --> 33:41.520
Hey, Chris,
where are you?

33:41.520 --> 33:42.687
I can't find my phone.

33:42.687 --> 33:43.688
Chris: Sean, get down!

33:43.688 --> 33:45.557
[ Gunshots ]

33:45.557 --> 33:52.731
♪♪

33:52.731 --> 33:54.299
Are you hit?

33:54.299 --> 33:56.268
No. You?
No.

33:56.268 --> 33:58.270
We got to move.
Out the back. Let's go. Go.

33:58.270 --> 34:06.912
♪♪

34:06.912 --> 34:15.287
♪♪

34:15.287 --> 34:23.929
♪♪

34:23.929 --> 34:25.764
Go, go, go, go, go.

34:25.764 --> 34:35.707
♪♪

34:35.707 --> 34:45.650
♪♪

34:45.650 --> 34:46.918
[ Clatter ]

34:46.918 --> 34:49.955
♪♪

34:49.955 --> 34:53.158
[ Gunshots ]

34:53.158 --> 35:01.766
♪♪

35:01.766 --> 35:10.241
♪♪

35:10.241 --> 35:18.583
♪♪

35:18.583 --> 35:20.051
[ Music stops ]

35:27.859 --> 35:30.228
[ Pounding on door ]

35:30.228 --> 35:33.031
[ Gunshots ]

35:33.031 --> 35:38.203
♪♪

35:38.203 --> 35:40.372
Lucy: Police!
Drop the weapon!

35:40.372 --> 35:47.812
♪♪

35:47.812 --> 35:49.280
[ Knock on door ]

35:49.280 --> 35:50.815
Chris?
Lucy?

35:50.815 --> 35:52.183
It's safe to come out.

35:52.183 --> 35:53.218
Is Del Monte with you?

35:53.218 --> 35:54.653
Yeah, I'm here.

35:54.653 --> 36:00.358
♪♪

36:00.358 --> 36:02.193
Are you okay?

36:02.193 --> 36:04.863
Yeah.
No.

36:04.863 --> 36:06.398
I could really use
a drink.

36:09.334 --> 36:12.203
I know today was rough,
but if it helps,

36:12.203 --> 36:14.406
it was not the worst
Plain Clothes Day story

36:14.406 --> 36:15.240
I've ever heard.

36:15.240 --> 36:16.541
It's not?
No.

36:16.541 --> 36:19.210
But it was
the most unique.

36:19.210 --> 36:20.979
And because
I pulled the plug,

36:20.979 --> 36:23.381
you're gonna have to do it
all again next week.

36:23.381 --> 36:24.883
Great.

36:24.883 --> 36:26.017
Hopefully I won't make
as many mistakes.

36:26.017 --> 36:27.285
Yeah,
that would be good.

36:27.285 --> 36:29.087
Yeah.
[ Laughs ]

36:29.087 --> 36:31.456
No. Unh-unh.

36:31.456 --> 36:33.258
Point another camera
in my face,

36:33.258 --> 36:36.061
and I will arrest you
for invasion of privacy.

36:36.061 --> 36:38.530
Just wanted to say bravo
for today, guys.

36:38.530 --> 36:40.732
The footage we got
was money.

36:40.732 --> 36:42.267
Harper,
the camera loves you.

36:42.267 --> 36:43.601
How would you feel about having
your very own makeup team?

36:43.601 --> 36:45.770
Morris,
can I talk to you?

36:47.238 --> 36:48.707
Have a good night.

36:48.707 --> 36:51.042
I will see you tomorrow.

36:51.042 --> 36:52.844
But I better not see you.

36:55.447 --> 36:56.915
Aaron --
No, man.

36:56.915 --> 36:59.451
You need to shut up
and listen, okay?

36:59.451 --> 37:01.419
That film that you shot of me
and Mr. Hayes today --

37:01.419 --> 37:03.254
it never sees
the light of day.

37:03.254 --> 37:04.422
Well, Aaron,
it's too good not to use.

37:04.422 --> 37:05.924
I don't care.

37:05.924 --> 37:08.326
His pain is not a commodity,
and neither is mine.

37:08.326 --> 37:10.328
Then why did you decide
to do the show?

37:10.328 --> 37:11.429
Because I need
to get my life back.

37:11.429 --> 37:14.099
But this --
this won't do that, okay?

37:14.099 --> 37:15.633
So you're gonna destroy
those memory cards

37:15.633 --> 37:17.602
or you and me --
we're gonna have a real problem.

37:17.602 --> 37:19.437
You threatening
to hurt me?

37:19.437 --> 37:20.538
No.

37:20.538 --> 37:22.307
To fire you.

37:22.307 --> 37:24.109
Those cards belong
to Thorsen Media,

37:24.109 --> 37:25.877
and last time I checked,
I'm the only person

37:25.877 --> 37:27.612
in this conversation
with that name.

37:29.647 --> 37:34.753
♪♪

37:34.753 --> 37:36.488
[ Knock on door ]

37:36.488 --> 37:38.957
[ Groans ]

37:38.957 --> 37:40.525
How are you doing?

37:40.525 --> 37:42.527
Oh, I'm fine, Lucy.

37:42.527 --> 37:44.496
♪ Trouble only finds me ♪

37:44.496 --> 37:45.663
Um, we should check
your vitals.

37:45.663 --> 37:47.132
No,
you don't have to --

37:47.132 --> 37:48.967
♪ Whenever I'm alone ♪

37:48.967 --> 37:51.503
That's actually
very nice.

37:51.503 --> 37:53.404
Pulse is good, steady.

37:53.404 --> 37:55.340
Well, that's me --

37:55.340 --> 37:57.509
good and steady.

37:57.509 --> 37:59.644
Your heart rate's
a little fast.

37:59.644 --> 38:01.346
It's still
strong and manly, right?

38:01.346 --> 38:03.515
Oh, yeah. 100%.

38:03.515 --> 38:05.583
[ Laughs ]

38:05.583 --> 38:07.886
♪ Who's tearing who to parts ♪

38:07.886 --> 38:11.556
Um...

38:11.556 --> 38:15.193
why did you try to give me
the witness list?

38:15.193 --> 38:16.895
Were you doing it
because you thought

38:16.895 --> 38:18.563
it was the right thing
to do,

38:18.563 --> 38:22.700
or were you trying
to impress me?

38:22.700 --> 38:25.203
♪ Never let you down ♪

38:25.203 --> 38:29.207
I, um...plead the fifth.

38:29.207 --> 38:31.009
♪ Like you let me down ♪

38:31.009 --> 38:32.610
[ Laughs ]

38:32.610 --> 38:34.379
Okay.
Mm-hmm.

38:34.379 --> 38:36.181
Hitter flipped on Rubio.

38:36.181 --> 38:37.715
Lopez picked him up
20 minutes ago.

38:37.715 --> 38:39.818
Another mob boss on his way
to life in prison.

38:39.818 --> 38:42.587
Good. But there's gonna be
some follow-up you need to do.

38:42.587 --> 38:44.589
I know. Talked it through
with the Captain.

38:44.589 --> 38:47.358
I know all about the Sergeants'
staff meeting on Mondays,

38:47.358 --> 38:49.427
the Captains' meetings
on Fridays.

38:49.427 --> 38:50.762
They provide lunch
from Molly's Steakhouse.

38:50.762 --> 38:53.598
Never order the fish.
See? I got it.

38:53.598 --> 38:55.767
And you'll be -- you'll be back
before you know it.

38:55.767 --> 38:57.368
♪ If only for a moment ♪

38:57.368 --> 38:59.404
It's not I don't think
you can do it.

38:59.404 --> 39:01.706
It's just --
You just have trouble
letting go.

39:01.706 --> 39:04.509
I know.
But this is good.

39:04.509 --> 39:06.845
You know, it's like a trial run
for retirement.

39:06.845 --> 39:08.379
♪ It's just
that I'm not over it ♪

39:08.379 --> 39:10.415
You're colluding
with Luna now?

39:10.415 --> 39:11.716
That has been going on
for a long time.

39:11.716 --> 39:12.717
Oh, my goodness.
[ Both laugh ]

39:12.717 --> 39:13.751
[ Knock on door ]

39:13.751 --> 39:14.752
Dinner is served.

39:14.752 --> 39:16.254
That's my cue.

39:16.254 --> 39:17.755
Thanks, man.
See ya, take care.
Yep.

39:17.755 --> 39:20.458
Grilled chicken, rice,
and veggies.

39:20.458 --> 39:21.793
I ordered a burger.

39:21.793 --> 39:23.027
♪ Let me down ♪

39:23.027 --> 39:24.562
You're colluding
with Luna now, too?

39:24.562 --> 39:26.431
No! No.

39:26.431 --> 39:27.966
Does that mean
you don't want it?

39:27.966 --> 39:30.235
Maybe later.
Alright.

39:30.235 --> 39:31.836
I'll just set it right here
for you.

39:31.836 --> 39:33.438
Thank you.
Alright. Good night.

39:33.438 --> 39:36.007
Nolan.

39:36.007 --> 39:39.410
A few months ago, you were
determined to be an F. T. O.

39:39.410 --> 39:42.580
Lately,
you hardly mention it.

39:42.580 --> 39:44.249
Change your mind?
Oh, no.

39:44.249 --> 39:45.450
No, not at all.

39:45.450 --> 39:46.818
Um, I've been working hard
behind the scenes,

39:46.818 --> 39:48.286
getting myself ready.

39:48.286 --> 39:50.421
Tim's been giving me lots
of great advice.

39:50.421 --> 39:53.458
I've been hoping my work as
the union rep would help me out.

39:53.458 --> 39:55.426
It will.

39:55.426 --> 39:58.596
So will focusing
on one area.

39:58.596 --> 40:02.967
Robbery, narcotics, hostage
negotiation, whatever you want.

40:02.967 --> 40:06.070
Become the department's
foremost expert at it.

40:07.438 --> 40:10.775
Specialized knowledge jumps you
to the front of the line.

40:10.775 --> 40:12.777
Yes, sir.

40:12.777 --> 40:15.613
Good advice.

40:15.613 --> 40:17.649
I will let you
get some sleep,

40:17.649 --> 40:19.284
unless there's anything else
you need?

40:19.284 --> 40:21.452
No, I'm good.
Thank you.

40:21.452 --> 40:22.854
♪ Oh oh oh oh ♪

40:22.854 --> 40:24.455
♪ Oh oh oh oh ♪

40:24.455 --> 40:26.858
Um...

40:26.858 --> 40:29.627
you're gonna want to replay
that fight over and over again,

40:29.627 --> 40:32.096
looking for a way
it could have ended differently.

40:33.464 --> 40:35.133
There will be plenty of time
for that.

40:35.133 --> 40:36.467
Tonight, just sleep.

40:36.467 --> 40:38.136
I'll try.

40:38.136 --> 40:42.273
♪♪

40:42.273 --> 40:44.509
♪ Oh oh oh oh oh oh ♪

41:00.058 --> 41:02.193
Busted!
Oh!

41:02.193 --> 41:04.362
What are you doing up?

41:04.362 --> 41:05.964
Waiting for you.

41:11.336 --> 41:13.538
How's Wade?

41:13.538 --> 41:15.940
He hurts,
but he'll be okay.

41:15.940 --> 41:18.142
And you?

41:18.142 --> 41:19.510
I'll be okay, too.

41:19.510 --> 41:23.514
Just...reopened some wounds
I thought had healed.

41:23.514 --> 41:25.850
Do you want
to talk about it?

41:25.850 --> 41:27.151
No.

41:27.151 --> 41:28.987
Okay.
Then come to bed.

41:28.987 --> 41:31.923
Honestly, I-I don't think
I could even sleep right now.

41:31.923 --> 41:34.592
Oh.
Do you want to finish
the portrait?

41:34.592 --> 41:37.395
God, no. I don't even want
to look at it anymore.

41:37.395 --> 41:38.596
Why not?

41:38.596 --> 41:39.998
Because it's awful.

41:39.998 --> 41:41.532
Oh.

41:41.532 --> 41:43.134
I refuse
to believe that.

41:43.134 --> 41:47.138
You are
the most talented person I know.

41:47.138 --> 41:48.539
It's actually annoying.

41:48.539 --> 41:51.909
Well, my winning streak
has officially ended.

41:53.411 --> 41:55.980
♪♪

41:55.980 --> 41:57.582
Oh, thank God.

41:57.582 --> 41:59.384
What?

41:59.384 --> 42:01.953
It's terrible.
I barely look human.

42:01.953 --> 42:04.022
You could
at least pretend.

42:04.022 --> 42:05.023
[ Laughing ]
No, I couldn't.

42:05.023 --> 42:07.225
But this is great.
This is great.

42:07.225 --> 42:09.594
Oh, this is so great.

42:09.594 --> 42:10.928
What are you doing?

42:10.928 --> 42:12.430
I'm gonna hang this up.

42:12.430 --> 42:14.232
It's -- It's proof that
